 What We are Watching

 Folk to first-time

 A moment from Kasba Arghya?s Chandrabati 

 Chandrabati

 In this adaptation of the Chandrabati-Jayananda love story from the Mymensingha Geetika, an oral epic of Bangladesh, Kasba Arghya has retained the folklore structure as much as possible. Sima Ghosh features in a solo act supported by a chorus. Directed by Manish Mitra.

 Catch it at Eastern Zonal Cultural Centre, March 6, 6 pm

 Death of a Godot

 Inspired by Samuel Beckett?s Waiting for Godot, this is a production from the newly formed five-member group PlayMakers. Directed by Bodhisatwa Dasgupta, a bunch of college-goers will stage the role reversals.

 Catch it at Gyan Manch, March 10, 6.30 pm

 Rajnaitik Hatya

 The Pancham Vaidic production is based on Jean-Paul Sartre?s Les Mains Sales. Set in Europe during World War II, the play brings out the ethical and political dilemma of an idealist. Directed by Saoli Mitra.

 Catch it at Academy of Fine Arts, March 5, 10 am




